roblem and enclose your code within delimiters.\n```python\nclass Solution:\n    def minimizeArrayValue(self, nums: List[int]) -> int:\n        \n```\n\n### Answer: (use the provided format with backticks)\n", "response": "```python\nfrom typing import List\nimport math\n\nclass Solution:\n    def minimizeArrayValue(self, nums: List[int]) -> int:\n        total_sum = 0\n        max_val = 0\n        \n        for i, num in enumerate(nums):\n            total_sum += num\n            # Calculate the maximum value of the prefix average (ceiling of total_sum / (i + 1))\n            max_val = max(max_val, math.ceil(total_sum / (i + 1)))\n        \n        return max_val\n```\n\n### Explanation:\nThe solution leverages the idea that the optimal strategy involves distributing the values in such a way that the maximum value in the array is minimized. By calculating the prefix sum and taking the ceiling of the average for each prefix, we can determine the minimum possible value of the maximum integer in the array after performing the allowed operations. This approach ensures that the solution is efficient with a time complexity of O(n).", "estimated_date": 1665273600000}